      "content": "i just dont want to deal with the hassle of going back to the clinic if it's nothing big. it's not really painful, just slightly tender. honestly the yellow stuff is very little, like just a tiny bit on the bandage. wouldn't some neosporin or similar antibiotic ointment from the chemist be enough to kill any bacteria and stop it from getting worse? it seems like a pretty standard thing to do for a small cut.",
